resources NI(31),FI(10)
notes
PIs: Kazuo Shiokawa, Yoshizumi Miyoshi, Shin-ichiro Oyama (STEL), Esa Turunen (SGO)

This experiment focuses on causality to produce hard-particle precipitation and
its effects on the ionosphere, thermosphere, and atmosphere from midnight after
substorm onset to the late morning. VHF (looking at north) and UHF (up B)
collaborate with optical instruments at the site. Auroral activity in the clear
sky is desirable. Two of the three UHF requests will be cancelled, dependent on
the condition.


The requested experiment windows are:
Feb 16: 2300-2400 (VHF), 2300-2400 (UHF)
Feb 17: 0000-1100, 2300-2400 (VHF), 0000-0500, 2300-2400 (UHF)
Feb 18: 0000-1000, 2300-2400 (VHF), 0000-0500, 2300-2400 (UHF)
Feb 19: 0000-1100 (VHF), 0000-0500 (UHF)
